SIMPLE: perennial
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perennial
<hw>Per*en"ni*al</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧r*⟦ecr⟧n"n⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>perennis</ets> that lasts the whole year
through; <ets>per</ets> through + <ets>annus</ets> year. See
<er>Per-</er>, and <er>Annual</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lasting or
continuing through the year; <as>as, <ex>perennial</ex>
fountains</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Continuing without cessation or intermission;
perpetual; unceasing; never failing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>perennial</qex> existence of bodies corporate.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Continuing more than two years;
<as>as, a <ex>perennial</ex> steam, or root, or plant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Perpetual; unceasing; never failing; enduring;
continual; permanent; uninterrupted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perennial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Perennial
<hw>Per*en"ni*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A perennial
plant; a plant which lives or continues more than two years, whether it
retains its leaves in winter or not.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perennially</ent>⟦br⟧
